@@ -0,0 +1,189 @@
+# API session sync handoff
+
+This document describes the Hermes API-server surfaces a desktop/mobile/web client can use to keep multiple clients synchronized with the same live Hermes session.
+
+## Goals covered
+
+- Re-open a session after app close/tab switch/device switch.
+- Receive current persisted history immediately.
+- Join a session while a run is already streaming and catch up on missed deltas/tool events.
+- Keep more than one client attached without stealing events from the initiating client.
+- Resume after reconnect from durable cursors.
+
+## Primary endpoint: session subscription SSE
+
+```http
+GET /api/sessions/{session_id}/subscribe
+Authorization: Bearer <API_SERVER_KEY>
+```
+
+For browser `EventSource`, where custom headers are awkward, the API server also accepts query-token auth:
+
+```http
+GET /api/sessions/{session_id}/subscribe?access_token=<API_SERVER_KEY>
+```
+
+The response is `text/event-stream`. The first event is always `session.snapshot`.
+
+```text
+event: session.snapshot
+data: { ...snapshot... }
+```
+
+Snapshot shape:
+
+```json
+{
+  "object": "hermes.session.snapshot",
+  "session_id": "api_...",
+  "session": { "id": "api_...", "title": "...", "message_count": 2, "...": "..." },
+  "messages": [
+    { "id": 1, "role": "user", "content": "...", "items": [...] },
+    { "id": 2, "role": "assistant", "content": "...", "items": [...] }
+  ],
+  "items": [
+    { "id": "msg:1", "type": "message", "role": "user", "content": "..." }
+  ],
+  "latest_event_cursor": "123",
+  "active_run": {
+    "object": "hermes.session.run",
+    "run_id": "run_...",
+    "session_id": "api_...",
+    "status": "running",
+    "last_seq": 4,
+    "draft": "partial assistant text",
+    "reasoning": "partial reasoning/tool progress text",
+    "tool_status": "terminal…"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+After the snapshot, the stream emits two kinds of catch-up/live events:
+
+1. Durable session events from `state.db` (`session.item.upserted`, `run.completed`, etc.). These carry a global `cursor` field.
+2. Replayable active-run events from `response_store.db` (`run.started`, `message.started`, `assistant.delta`, `tool.progress`, `tool.started`, `tool.completed`, `assistant.completed`, `run.completed`, `done`, `error`). These carry a per-run integer `seq` field.
+
+Example run event:
+
+```text
+event: assistant.delta
+data: {"run_id":"run_...","session_id":"api_...","seq":3,"message_id":"msg_...","delta":"hello"}
+```
+
+When the latest run for a session changes while the subscription is open, the stream emits:
+
+```text
+event: run.switch
+data: {"session_id":"api_...","run":{...new run snapshot...}}
+```
+
+The client should reset its per-run `seq` cursor to `0` for that new `run_id`, then apply subsequent run events normally.
+
+## Resume / reconnect cursors
+
+The endpoint accepts independent cursors:
+
+```http
+GET /api/sessions/{session_id}/subscribe?after=<session_event_cursor>&run_after=<last_run_seq>
+```
+
+Aliases:
+
+- `cursor` is accepted as an alias for `after`.
+- `after_seq` is accepted as an alias for `run_after`.
+
+Recommended client state to persist per session:
+
+```json
+{
+  "session_id": "api_...",
+  "session_event_cursor": "123",
+  "run_id": "run_...",
+  "run_seq": 7
+}
+```
+
+On reconnect:
+
+1. Open `/api/sessions/{session_id}/subscribe?after=<session_event_cursor>&run_after=<run_seq>`.
+2. Replace/merge local session metadata/history from `session.snapshot`.
+3. Apply all subsequent events in order.
+4. Update `session_event_cursor` whenever an event has `cursor`.
+5. Update `run_id`/`run_seq` whenever a run event has `run_id`/`seq`.
+6. If `run.switch` arrives, replace `run_id` with the new run and reset `run_seq` to `0` before applying new run events.
+
+If no `after` cursor is supplied, Hermes treats the snapshot as the history catch-up point and starts durable session events from the snapshot-time cursor. This avoids duplicating old persisted messages that are already present in `messages`/`items`. Active-run events still replay from `run_after` (default `0`) so a mid-stream subscriber catches the current assistant deltas.
+
+## Starting work in a session
+
+Use the persisted session stream endpoint to start a turn:
+
+```http
+POST /api/sessions/{session_id}/chat/stream
+Content-Type: application/json
+Authorization: Bearer <API_SERVER_KEY>
+
+{"message":"do the task"}
+```
+
+The initiating client may consume that response directly, but it does not have to be the only consumer. Any other client can call `/api/sessions/{session_id}/subscribe` and receive the same replayable active-run events from durable storage.
+
+For non-initiating clients:
+
+1. Connect to `/api/sessions/{session_id}/subscribe`.
+2. Render `session.snapshot.messages` immediately.
+3. If `session.snapshot.active_run.status` is `queued` or `running`, keep rendering incoming `assistant.delta`/tool/run events.
+
+## Existing companion endpoints
+
+These remain useful for focused workflows:
+
+- `GET /api/sessions` — list sessions. Each row includes lightweight live state:
+  - `active`: true only when Hermes is actively processing/queued/stopping for that session.
+  - `status`: `processing`, `idle`, `interrupted`, `completed`, etc.
+  - `sync_state`: detailed session state plus pending tool-call ids and cursor.
+  - `active_run`: the current queued/running/waiting/stopping run snapshot, or `null`.
+- `POST /api/sessions` — create an empty session.
+- `GET /api/sessions/{session_id}` — session metadata with the same live-state fields as the list row.
+- `GET /api/sessions/{session_id}/messages` — persisted message history only.
+- `GET /api/sessions/{session_id}/active-run` — latest run snapshot only.
+- `GET /api/session-runs/{run_id}/events?after=<seq>` — per-run replay SSE when a client already knows the run id.
+- `GET /v1/sessions/{session_id}/items` — stable item projection.
+- `GET /v1/sessions/{session_id}/events?after=<cursor>` — durable session-event replay only.
+- `GET /v1/session_events/firehose` — websocket firehose for global sync/replication consumers.
+- `POST /v1/session_events/ack` — acknowledge global firehose cursor after an external consumer durably stores events.
+
+## Client rendering notes
+
+- Treat `messages` in `session.snapshot` as the authoritative persisted transcript at attach time.
+- Treat `items` as the normalized render model for message/tool-call/tool-result display.
+- Accumulate `assistant.delta` events by `message_id` for the current in-progress assistant draft.
+- On `assistant.completed`, replace the draft with the completed content.
+- On `run.completed`, reconcile with `messages` in that payload if present; Hermes includes the interleaved assistant/tool transcript for the completed turn when available.
+- Tool events may arrive as both renderable run events (`tool.progress`, `tool.started`, `tool.completed`) and durable item upserts (`session.item.upserted`) depending on the path. Use stable item ids and tool_call ids to de-dupe.
+
+## Implementation pointers
+
+- API-server adapter: `gateway/platforms/api_server.py`
+  - `_handle_session_subscribe` implements the new snapshot + live SSE endpoint.
+  - `_handle_session_chat_stream` persists replayable per-run events into `ResponseStore.session_run_events`.
+  - `_record_live_tool_session_item` publishes provisional tool call/result item upserts into `SessionDB.session_events`.
+- Durable stores:
+  - `hermes_state.py` / `SessionDB.session_events` for session items and global cursor-based sync.
+  - `ResponseStore.session_runs` and `ResponseStore.session_run_events` in `response_store.db` for per-run assistant deltas and run lifecycle replay.
+- Capability discovery:
+  - `GET /v1/capabilities` advertises `features.session_subscribe_sse: true` and `endpoints.session_subscribe`.
+
+## Verified behavior
+
+Regression coverage lives in `tests/gateway/test_session_api.py`:
+
+- `test_session_subscribe_sends_snapshot_and_replays_active_run`
+- `test_session_subscribe_streams_events_written_after_connect`
+- Existing session chat stream/replay tests cover durable run events and active-run snapshots.
+
+Verified with:
+
+```bash
+scripts/run_tests.sh tests/gateway/test_session_api.py
+```
